question: Hi❤️ Can I have a ship pls? I'm ENFJ,5’7”,the eldest of 4,making me reliable & a good leader.Very caring,affectionate,kind,really nice a friendly to everyone,strong both physically & mentally. I'm a good listener so as a good adviser.I love sharing my love w/my fam & ppl I care.I'll fill what they lack & I'll cut down what that's too much.I adore animals,children & LOVE cuddling,coffee.I can cook too.I'm always there for my sibling.Smile's always on my face & I hope everyone can smile,too.Tysm!

AND FOR THE GRAND FINALE, CAN I GET A FUCKEN DRUM ROLL PLEASSEEEE,

i ship youuuu, WITH Kim Namjoon!!

wow, you’re so good with just getting to the point of yourself. girl, i feel like you are the perfect ideal for him, well except i don’t know if you’re feminine like he described, anywaaays, idgaf. this is my opinion anyways IM SO STUPID KNDKSJDD.

you’re eldest out of 4, having good leadership skills, i kinda feel for you even if you take blames for your siblings. i do that, but i’m the youngest T-T. and it’s not fair. i think to know you’re responsible for your siblings, and being responsible shows you’re caring, when that is shown, namjoon would adore you for it. a lot of people tend not to care. i admire you being strong both physically and mentally, becaaauuse, GO BEAT TF OUT OF THIS BITCH THAT LIKES TO START SHIT WITH ME LOLLL, jk i’m a wussy T-T, JK YOU THOUGHT. now for soemthing i think namjoon would adore you for, i also adore you for this, is that you’re strong of your mental mind. basically, your mind is stable. summary: BTS on Ellen was cringey at best and racist at worst. No new questions, they orchestrated the entire fangirl schtick again,...
body: BTS on Ellen was cringey at best and racist at worst. No new questions, they orchestrated the entire fangirl schtick again, subtitles were like [inaudible] [Korean] but they bothered with the English and Spanish lines, the scare had no relevance or positive impact. Ignorant Ellen didn’t even care about their names, instead it was about Friends because that’s how RM learned English to cater to the US (…the present was a mere reward), the dating girls trolling thing again which is problematic on several levels, despite decent camera work too much audience focus… It’s “Biggest boyband in the world” for the fame and attention it brings, not “great artists” or “great personalities”, “great work (for 5 years)”. That’s why none of their progress as musicians was discussed. And well, Ellen trying to be the 8th member… we talked about how I also noticed how insolent these types of hosts/interviewers are thinking they can get the clout in one second that BTS had to work for years and years. It’s not funny. I also noticed how selective they are about their audience aka contradicting themselves when they say BTS is global. No, they want them to be “exotic” and for [Asian] females only - lowkey homophobic and stereotyping women’s taste all while distancing them from a diverse international audience. And I mean, Ellen not supporting same-sex attraction… what?! There was one token guy and one black girl in the crowd. It’s an irony that the lead song is Fake Love, that’s what America is giving them for their piece of the hype while treating them like rubbish. It’s just to leech off ARMY’s energy. I’m sorry that BTS had to sit through that while simultaneously giving their best on stage because unlike Ellen, they did not disappoint. What else is new.

That’s why none of their progress as musicians was discussed. And well, Ellen trying to be the 8th member… we talked about how I also noticed how insolent these types of hosts/interviewers are thinking they can get the clout in one second that BTS had to work for years and years. It’s not funny. I also noticed how selective they are about their audience aka contradicting themselves when they say BTS is global. No, they want them to be “exotic” and for [Asian] females only - lowkey homophobic and stereotyping women’s taste all while distancing them from a diverse international audience. And I mean, Ellen not supporting same-sex attraction… what?! There was one token guy and one black girl in the crowd. It’s an irony that the lead song is Fake Love, that’s what America is giving them for their piece of the hype while treating them like rubbish. It’s just to leech off ARMY’s energy. I’m sorry that BTS had to sit through that while simultaneously giving their best on stage because unlike Ellen, they did not disappoint. What else is new.
